<TEXT>
ayatollah marashi najafi one of irans 
top islamic authorities has died of a heart attack tehran radio 
reported thursday he was 96 
the broadcast monitored in nicosia said he died wednesday in 
his home in qom an islamic holy city in western iran 
iranian president hashemi rafsanjani declared a threeday 
national mourning period in najafis memory 
najafi was born in 1894 the city of najaf iraq 
he came to iran in 1923 on a pilgrimage to the shrine of the 
shiite moslem saint imam reza 
after a threemonth stay in tehran he was invited to teach at 
the renowned qom theological seminary 
he remained in iran and came to be regarded as a grand 
ayatollah or supreme shiite moslem authority in recognition of 
his learning 
during his years in iran najafi wrote many treatises on islam 
and shiism 
</TEXT>
