<TEXT>
a chinese businessmans association has been 
indicted on charges it ran a multimilliondollar illegal gambling 
operation from several us cities the federal government 
announced thursday 
the 34count indictment names the national on leong chinese 
merchants association in new york and its chicago houston and new 
york chapters as well as 29 individuals said fred l foreman 
us attorney for the northern district of illinois 
the national on leong directed and controlled illegal 
casinostyle gambling games such as fan tan pai gow and 13 card 
maintained by several of the local chapters said the 98page 
indictment handed down wednesday 
the 29 individuals are listed as residents of detroit 
minneapolis pittsburgh houston atlanta chicago and new york 
according to a statement released with the document 
the group allgedly used a new york street gang the ghost 
shadows for protection and to resolve disputes 
the association and some of the individuals were charged with 
racketeering conspiracy conspiracy to bribe a witness and 
conspiracy to bribe a chicago area judge 
some also were charged with illegal gambling and conspiracy to 
defraud the us government by obstructing the internal revenue 
service 
the government sought to seize on leong buildings in chicago 
new york and houston as well as 115 million in proceeds the 
indictment said came from illegal gambling 
foreman said in a telephone interview that on leong has run a 
gambling operation for at least six years and that the indictments 
resulted from a 2year investigation 
