<TEXT>
the serial killings in gainesville fla 
recall the terror that gripped californians during the night 
stalker murders a reign that ended five years ago today 
on aug 31 1985 texas drifter richard ramirez was captured by 
an angry mob that recognized him from news photos capping a summer 
of random nocturnal attacks 
the grisly string of satanic crimes still haunts the legal 
system and those who became entwined in one of the most complex 
prosecutions ever 
its not over people think because theyre not reading it in 
the paper anymore that its over said deputy district attorney 
p philip halpin whose career became captive to the ramirez case 
there will be many more anniversaries before this case reaches 
its resolution unfortunately 
the appeal process has just begun for the 30yearold ramirez 
convicted of 13 murders and 30 felonies ramirez also faces trial 
soon in san francisco in a single slaying there 
in spite of winning ramirezs conviction and death sentence last 
september halpin remains assigned to the case fulltime he works 
in an office filled with transcripts of marathon court proceedings 
for use in the appeal which is automatic in deathpenalty cases 
how long will it take to resolve the appeal were talking 
years said halpin 
ramirez is being held in the county jail in san francisco where 
deputy district attorney eugene sweeters said he hasnt caused 
any trouble there as far as i know 
ramirezs reign of terror ended when east los angeles residents 
captured him after he tried to pull a woman from her car by the 
time police arrived a crowd was shouting kill him kill him 
officers formed a human chain to protect ramirez from the mob 
residents said the night stalker held all of them captive 
throughout that steamy summer when they kept windows and doors shut 
tight in fear 
as in the gainesville slayings it was through unlocked windows 
and doors that the stalker entered homes he raped killed and 
mutilated his victims 
a womans eyes were gouged out after she was killed by the 
night stalker a man was murdered in his bed and his wife was 
raped beside the dead body 
there were signs of devil worship a pentagram drawn on the 
wall at one murder scene and survivors accounts of being ordered 
to swear to satan 
a preliminary hearing in 1986 disclosed the horror of the 
victims ordeals and resulted in witnessstand identifications of 
ramirez as the killer 
legal maneuvers by a series of defense attorneys delayed 
ramirezs trial a succession of judges presided before superior 
court judge michael tynan took charge and saw the case through a 
yearlong trial 
at the very end a juror was slain during deliberations defense 
lawyers sought a mistrial but the judge ruled the killing in a 
domestic dispute was unrelated to the case and ordered jurors to 
proceed they recommended the death penalty which tynan imposed 
ramirez passed up the opportunity to testify preventing 
hopedfor glimpses of the killers mind and motivation he chose to 
remain a mystery spouting slogans of devilworship 
i am beyond good and evil i will be avenged lucifer dwells 
in us all thats it ramirez said before he was led off to 
prison 
halpin said he has concluded the serial killer was really a 
smalltime burglar out of control 
he noted that ramirez failed to fit the usual serial killer 
profile of someone who always kills with the same weapon and whose 
victims are similar 
halpin suggested that investigators in the gainesville case may 
be facing problems similar to those that stymied the night 
stalker task force for months 
frankly law enforcement wasnt ready for a night stalker 
said halpin every study of serial murderers led to conclusions 
that didnt apply to this case 
</TEXT>
