<TEXT>
few nightclub comics have the nerve to 
jump off the stage and snatch a steak from a fan at a frontrow 
table 
winston the wonder dog did 
winstons routine was not sophisticated dog acts rarely are 
but his impression of barbara bush was a crowd pleaser and 
audiences roared when he lay on his back and punched the air with 
boxing gloveclad feet 
the old english sheepdog who traveled the nations comedy clubs 
and college campuses for six years died at wednesday at age 11 
he was the straight guy and i just had to make whatever he 
did funny seattle comedian earl burks said thursday as he 
prepared for his first show since winstons death 
winston was humanely destroyed by a henderson veterinarian after 
suffering symptoms of old age that forced his retirement four 
months ago and worsened steadily since burks said a younger 
sheepdog took over winstons act 
winston the wonder dog performed in las vegas 47 states and 
canada where he once spent a night in jail and entertained the 
local police burks said 
the dogs photograph appeared in rolling stone and people 
magazine and dozens of local newspapers he was on the nationally 
televised show star search 
winstons talents included dancing on his hind legs and 
answering questions such as whats the top of a house 
called answer roof 
it was just real stupid but it was funny burks said 
sometimes when he would bark into the microphone he would just 
keep on and on because he could hear himself it was so goofy that 
people would laugh 
with a wardrobe of wigs sunglasses and masks winston also 
impersonated the political personalities of the day including the 
ayatollah khomeini and the first lady and celebrities such as 
sammy davis jr stevie wonder and zsa zsa gabor 
the shaggy grayandwhite dogs large pliable mouth leant 
itself to manipulation by burks whose humor sometimes took a bawdy 
turn 
burks bought winston as a puppy when he needed material to fill 
time at a comedy club someone suggested he take his pet on stage 
there was a guy at a front table with a big steak burks 
said i turned my back and he was up on this guys table eating 
this steak they were laughing and applauding and i was thinking 
oh no im gonna get sued 
a dog star was born 
