<TEXT>
a prosecutor was shot in the head and killed 
thursday in a driveby slaying as he picked up doughnuts at a store 
near the bronx county courthouse but authorities said he was not 
the target of the gunman 
also thursday a former state senator 49yearold vander 
beatty was fatally shot in his office in the brooklyn borough 
the prosecutor 30yearold sean healy was hit once as he bent 
over to take a box of doughnuts from a store shelf said michael 
philbin chief of bronx detectives 
he certainly was not a target he happened to be in the wrong 
place at the wrong time philbin said 
philbin said police had been summoned to a location a block from 
the store about an hour before the shooting but no one was there 
when they arrived he said police theorized that the shooting and 
the dispute were linked but they did not know for certain 
late thursday a suspect in the shooting voluntarily surrendered 
to police in the bronx and was being questioned said officer mark 
warren a police spokesman no charges were brought immediately 
warren said 
