amin a palestinian 
electrician who fled kuwait after working there for 21 years 
returned home this week with three small bags and little hope for 
the future 
it was the second time amin had fled a military occupation the 
first time was after the israeli conquest of the west bank and gaza 
strip in the 1967 middle east war 
this time its more difficult for us than in 1967 said amin 
on wednesday noting that he lost 65000 in savings and property 
in kuwait and had little chance of finding a job in his hometown of 
ramallah in the west bank 
