<TEXT>
people who take their pills even if they are 
sugar pills are more likely to live than those who dont follow 
the doctors orders according to a study in a british medical 
journal 
dr ralph horwitz of the yale university school of medicine 
author of the lancet study published thursday said researchers 
cannot explain why people who take their medicine even placebos 
are more likely to live 
we need a better measure of the social and psychological 
features to explain why it is he said 
horwitz said his team of researchers analyzed a 1978 test on 
beta blockers often given after a heart attack to reduce the 
likelihood of further damage 
half of the studys participants were given the drug and the 
other half were given placebos 
horwitzs analysis of the study found that those who took their 
medicine placebo or drug had a higher survival rate than those 
who did not 
