supreme court ruling that allows police to make random checks for 
drunken drivers according to the american alliance for rights and 
responsibilities which surveyed state public safety officials 
most other states planned to step up enforcement for the weekend 
the group said 
president bush also declared it national drive for life weekend 
to push efforts against drunken driving which figures in about 
half of all traffic fatalities 
