at the oasis 100 miles south of the oil capital of dhahran 
the market was tired he said few of the meat camels for 
sale reached the top price of 400 
he did not attribute the low prices to iraqs aug 2 invasion of 
kuwait and the subsequent war tension on his countrys northern 
border 
its the heat said the 27yearold electrician with the 
aramco oil giant who tends camels in his native village on 
weekends august temperatures soar to 120 degrees 
but war was on everybodys mind allataibi conceded 
its all the people talk about first lets talk about peace 
then if theres no peace we can talk about war he said 
as he spoke young camels yowled in the background 
but the sellers seemed more intent on discussing the merits of a 
13000 racing camel than the conflict 
