embargo reported that oil is now being pumped from the north to 
aden to make up for the loss of iraqi and kuwaiti supplies 
british royal air force sources have reported that some iraqi 
combat jets have been flown to yemen for use if iraqi air bases are 
hit saleh has denied that 
yemen emerged as a potential flashpoint when us warships began 
shadowing iraqi oil tankers to aden enforcing the unsanctioned 
trade embargo against iraq 
yemens information minister mohammed ahmed garhoum denied 
british allegations that yemen violated the un sanctions by 
allowing an iraqi tanker the ain zalah to unload at aden 
he said in a telephone interview that the tanker partially 
unloaded before the sanctions but unloading stopped after the 
embargo resolution 
yemen last week ordered the expulsion of britains 
consulgeneral in aden douglas gordon after he was arrested 
photographing shipping at aden but the yemenis relented after 
strong british protests 
garhoum insisted its not true that yemen supports iraq 
yemen wants iraq to withdraw its forces from kuwait 
our position is clear our government underlines the necessity 
of respect for national sovereignty and we reject the use of 
force its only a summer cloud that will soon go away he said 
