<TEXT>
when the men of the 265th quartermaster 
detachment crossed the boundaries of this huge military base their 
teeth became the property and responsibility of the us army 
the tiny national guard water purification unit of 14 men has 
been activated for possible duty in saudi arabia the south 
carolina guardsmen face the potential of blazing desert heat and 
the uncertainties of geopolitics 
but first came the picks and pliers of a dentist known lovingly 
on base as the prince of pain 
six men had teeth pulled or cavities filled at the end of their 
first day of mobilization most were muttering and lisping through 
novocain and cotton gauze 
i guess yall have some pretty bad teeth said the units 
leader a sergeant named ronnie who is a probation officer in 
civilian life army security rules prohibit publication of the 
mens last names 
huh uhh ahh ernie another sergeant said opening his 
mouth to display the fact the bad teeth were no more 
thursdays tooth torture was an ignoble beginning for the 265th 
which received an emotional sendoff wednesday from allendale sc 
all the men are from allendale or the outlying communities of 
brunson and fairfax small towns about three hours drive from fort 
stewart 
despite the oppressive heat more than 1000 people nearly 20 
percent of allendales population turned out for a red white and 
blue bannered celebration of speeches and church choir songs each 
man of the unit was presented with a bible 
the celebration spilled into the next morning students from the 
local elementary and high schools lined the road to wave as the 
unit left for fort stewart with its three 15ton trucks fitted 
with equipment that uses filters and chemicals to purify water 
the callup of the 265th is a source of local pride south 
carolina has guard units that drive m1 tanks and fly apache 
helicopters but only the 265th has been activated an indication 
of the value clean drinking water will have for us troops in the 
mideast 
we know we can get the mission done said william a 
44yearold construction worker who served a tour of duty in 
vietnam 20 years ago there is another vietnam vet in the unit 
nearly half have seen duty in the regular military 
