that many people are no longer talking about whether there will 
be a coup but when 
faced with the crisis mrs aquino reversed a longstanding 
policy and said wednesday she was willing to negotiate a 
ceasefires with communist and military rebels the cabinet meets 
saturday to discuss prospects for a truce 
but there has been no clear statement from either military 
dissidents or the communist party on whether they would go along 
with a ceasefire 
furthermore political sources say defense secretary fidel ramos 
strongly opposes a truce saying it would undercut morale in the 
armed forces 
this apparent split has fueled rumors the armed forces may be 
planning a constitutional coup establishing some sort of 
militaryrun emergency commission that would run the country with 
mrs aquino as a figurehead 
ramos who crushed the six coup attempts has strongly denied 
the rumors and said thursday they were spread by dissidents to 
foment division in the government 
