<TEXT>
a federal appeals court overturned wayne 
newtons record 52 million libel judgment saying the jury didnt 
prove nbc news was deliberately false or reckless in suggesting the 
singer had ties to the mob 
in dismissing newtons lawsuit the 9th us circuit court of 
appeals ruled 30 thursday that any false impressions in the 1980 
broadcast did not result from the type of journalistic misconduct 
required for libel lawsuits by public figures 
the us supreme court has ruled public figures must prove that 
defamatory statements were either deliberate falsehoods or 
recklessly disregarded the truth 
newtons lawyer morton galane said he would not comment until 
he could reach newton 
a jury in las vegas found that nbcs story falsely implied that 
the mafia had helped newton buy the aladdin hotel and casino in 
exchange for a hidden interest 
