<DOCNO> AP900831-0090 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
german leaders met in a palace of german 
princes today and signed a treaty meant to reconcile the stark 
differences between their two nations just 33 days before they 
become one 
the document was signed by west german interior minister 
wolfgang schaeuble and east germanys top unity negotiator 
guenther krause 
earlier the cabinets of west german chancellor helmut kohl and 
east german prime minister lothar de maiziere formally approved the 
pact 
the treaty is the final blueprint for the framework of a united 
nation although it leaves many crucial issues to be decided by a 
united german government 
today we are fulfilling one of the last remaining hurdles to 
german unification de maiziere said moments before the pact was 
signed in a 17th century palace in east berlin 
the sweeping accord preserves east germanys liberal abortion 
law calls for a united berlin to be the capital of the new nation 
and guarantees some social programs for jobless east germans 
it gives western investors first claim to east german property 
a major development that economists say is necessary to revive the 
nations shattered economy 
the pact also allows east germany to maintain some control over 
the 6 million files of the former communist secret police a 
potentially explosive compilation of sinister secrets from the 
nations dark past 
overall the treaty reconciles fundamental legal and political 
differences between two nations that followed vastly different 
paths after they were carved from the conquered nazi empire 
the signing ceremony was held in the stately berlin palace the 
home of german crown princes who laid the foundation for the 
prussian empire of the 18th century like germany the palace was 
destroyed during world war ii and then rebuilt 
the signing took place on the eve of 51st anniversary of world 
war ii on sept 1 1939 hitlers forces invaded poland and 
france and england declared the war that eventually split germany 
the german states will become one on oct 3 when east germanys 
parliament invokes a clause that will allow it to accede to the 
larger nation 
germans in both territories will then elect a common government 
on dec 2 
that impending election date has created an enormous campaign 
battle between kohls conservative christian democrats and his main 
rival in the elections the leftleaning social democrats 
key aspects of the treaty particularly the sharp differences 
between east germanys liberal abortion law and west germanys 
tough one were held up by debate that threatened the pacts 
passage 
although such a treaty was not necessary for german unification 
failure to approve it would have meant that west german laws would 
have become automatically the law of a greater german land 
the treaty was considered an important psychological necessity 
for an east german nation that has been buffeted by enormous 
political and economic change in less than a year and which is 
about to lose its sovereignty and its identity 
the treaty is a companion piece to the economic pact that merged 
the currencies and economies of the german states on july 1 when 
east germany formally became a free market after four decades of 
socialism 
east german joblessness since then has skyrocketed as factories 
collapse in the face of western competition 
the document includes an important provision for the 
distribution of east german property 
tens of thousands of west germans who fled what is now east 
germany after the soviet invasion of world war ii have filed claims 
on their former property a prolonged process is planned to 
determine the validity of those claims on an individual basis 
the uncertainty of those many claims and who will be the 
potential owner of much east german property has been blamed for 
inhibiting western investment needed to provide jobs and replace 
the dying sectors of the east german economy 
under a previous agreement west germans are allowed to claim 
property in east germany that was seized from their families by the 
communists or lost when they fled to the west under the treaty 
signed today anyone who buys land in east germany for development 
purposes is protected from claims by previous owners or their 
heirs there will be a system worked out later to compensate people 
who dont get their land back because it is being developed 
commercially or because their claim would displace people living 
there 
the pact also includes a compromise on the volatile abortion 
question east germanys permissive law will remain in effect until 
a new german government passes a law for both nations in 1992 
it also settles at least for now a dispute between the two 
germanys over the disposition of the files compiled by the 
notorious secret police which kept sensitive information about 
millions of people some of them now leaders in the democratic 
government 
east germany and west germany both wanted control of the files 
a gold mine of espionage and terrorist intelligence under the 
compromise the united parliament will make the decision 
in the meantime the files will temporarily remain in what is 
now east germany under the custody of a west german official to be 
chosen by east germany 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

