affordability index declined from 1029 in june to 1023 last 
month that means a family with a median income of 34358 had 
1023 percent of the income needed to buy a medianpriced existing 
home costing 98400 
the median income was 34250 in june while the median price 
was 97500 
the median means half of the families earn more and half earn 
less or that half of the houses sell for more and half for less 
