vlok who heads the police also said rising crime could trigger 
violence between whites and blacks he said tension was being 
stoked by strikes black consumer boycotts and terrorist attacks 
fighting erupted aug 12 in black townships near johannesburg 
and raged for almost two weeks zulu followers of the conservative 
inkatha movement fought xhosas and other blacks loyal to the anc 
with axes spears guns and knives 
the two groups oppose south africas apartheid system of racial 
separation but are divided by leadership rivalry tribal loyalty 
and differing visions of a future south africa 
the government last week imposed emergency restrictions and sent 
in troops to aid police in the areas of violence police said 
friday the johannesburg townships were quiet 
