<TEXT>
german leaders on friday signed a treaty to 
reconcile their legal and constititutional differences before unity 
here are the main points of the 900page unification treaty 
east germany will avail itself of article 23 of the west german 
constitution to join its larger neighbor oct 3 
west germanys constitution takes effect in what is now east 
germany on the day of unity 
berlin is designated the capital of a united germany the 
decision on the location of the allgerman parliament and the seat 
of government will be determined after unification 
the 6 million files compiled by the stasi the former east 
german secret police are to remain in east germany for now the 
allgerman parliament is to decide on their future disposition 
the allgerman parliament is required to pass a new abortion 
law to reconcile the two vastly different rules that now exist in 
the two states each country retains its laws until the new rules 
take effect 
the two states recognize the inviolability of borders and the 
territorial integrity and sovereignty of all states in europe 
under a previous agreement west germans are allowed to claim 
property in east germany that was seized from their families by the 
communists or lost when they fled to the west under the treaty 
signed friday anyone who buys land in east germany for development 
purposes is protected from claims by previous owners or their 
heirs there will be a system worked out later to compensate people 
who dont get their land back because it is being developed 
commercially or because their claim would displace people living 
there 
treaties and agreements of the european economic community take 
effect on the former territory of east germany immediately after 
unification 
