than 1 million troops while south korea has 650000 
the north koreans also demand withdrawal of the 43000 us 
troops stationed in south korea under a mutual defense treaty but 
south korea opposes any drastic measures like arms cuts before an 
extended period of confidence building 
the two nations fought a threeyear war in the early 1950s 
their border is sealed without mail or direct communication 
they have held talks on and off since the early 1970s but failed 
to make major progress 
