much of which comes from europe and the united states many actors 
now work abroad 
the downturn has been sudden even considering the topsyturvy 
industry whose fortunes reflect four decades of political coups and 
economic instability 
in the 1940s and early 50s buenos aires was a sort of 
hollywood south five production companies churned out dozens of 
films a year mostly lowbrow comedies that were hits up and down 
the continent 
the 1980s in contrast saw serious films with political and 
