two romanian expatriates are trying to 
help cool passions that linger after the revolution by teaching 
western journalism to reporters who never had to distinguish fact 
from fiction 
under nicolae ceausescu communist authorities replaced the 
journalism department at bucharest university with an 
indoctrination course for party officials to make sure the 
propaganda machine ran smoothly 
the result even after the dictator was overthrown and executed 
in december is a polarized press that often inflames the public 
what passes for news is a onesided mix of opinion sprinkled 
with a few facts progovernment and opposition papers are equally 
guilty 
government spokesmen claim the opposition shames romania the 
independent daily romania libera began a recent response so we 
dont want the good of the country 
