teachers said his 140 students still have trouble distinguishing 
between fact and opinion 
its difficult to get them to understand that their opinions 
are irrelevant to objective reporting he said but they are 
enthusiastic about journalism and learning about the world 
outside 
his students some of whom worked in the statecontrolled media 
