ok class listen up if its labor day week it 
must be time for those annual television marathons on what ails 
public education 
happily cbs and public broadcasting are serving up two 
unusually engaging and informative backtoschool specials 
leading off is learning in america schools that work a 
twohour pbs offering appearing 911 pm edt wednesday sept 5 
reporter roger mudd guides us through four elementary schools that 
have defied odds and become special places that put kids first 
its a refreshing break for viewers awash in bad news about us 
schools 
the program shows classroom life in northview school a 
workingclass school in manhattan kan columbia park elementary 
school in landover md where 95 percent of students are black 
city magnet school a unique multiethnic school in lowell mass 
with studentrun banks courts and other features of a democratic 
freemarket society and lozano special emphasis school 98 percent 
hispanic where a toughminded principal has virtually eliminated 
absenteeism and boosted test scores 
city magnet is especially interesting a model of learning by 
doing for one period a day kids put aside their other academic 
chores and hold jobs in a mock democratic society that imitates 
real life students pay taxes hold jobs and sell goods and 
services a girl who hits another gets hauled before a studentrun 
court and gets a stiff fine 
most of all says one parent the school has heart a lot of 
heart 
mudd concludes by summarizing what makes all four schools 
excellent a devoted belief in the value of public education 
collegiality among teachers independence from school district 
bureaucrats and above all a commitment to the children 
themselves a respect for their selfesteem and the ability of each 
to learn 
by focusing on peaceful carefree elementary schools the pbs 
special exudes a feelgood air that would be far less plausible if 
the cameras were aimed at high schools 
and mudd dismisses perhaps too lightly the role of money in 
school reform 
still the pbs special succeeds admirably in showing why these 
schools work while so many others fail mudd handles the assignment 
with a deft unobtrusive touch wisely letting the pictures and 
action speak for themselves while keeping the focus clear with 
wellchosen commentary 
quite different and even more ambitious is cbss twohour 
offering americas toughest assignment solving the education 
crisis airing at 911 pm edt thursday anchored by the wise 
