too late the bank and federal regulators had to scramble to 
shore up the banks reputation saying it was solvent and denying 
that a takeover was pending 
already fighting to recover from new englands depressed real 
estate market that left it holding millions of dollars in bad 
loans the banks stock plummeted 385 percent to 1 a share from 
