discount fell 7 basis points to 736 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills fell to 774 percent as the discount fell 2 basis points to 
736 percent yields on oneyear bills fell to 776 percent as the 
discount fell 2 basis points to 724 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
