comsat aeronautical services and sony trans 
com inc friday announced that they will collaborate on the 
development of a new satellite service that will provide news 
updates and other information for international airline passengers 
a worldwide communications link for aircraft equipped for 
satellite reception will be available beginning in 1991 to keep 
travelers abreast of breaking news and international developments 
according to a joint statement by the companies 
the news and information will initially be targeted at 
international travelers and will be displayed as text and graphics 
an additional feature that will be available could allow 
travelers to receive messages from home or office because of the 
services ability to send directly to specific aircraft tail 
numbers 
