<TEXT>
genentech inc and roche 
holding ltd of switzerland said their 21 billion merger will go 
ahead as the result of an agreement friday with the federal trade 
commission 
the california biotechnology company and swiss pharmaceutical 
giant expected to complete the merger in which roche will acquire 
60 percent of genentechs stock on or about sept 7 
the companies said they entered into a consent decree with the 
ftc which conducted an antitrust law review of the merger 
announced in february and approved by 97 percent of genentechs 
shareholders in june 
the decree requires that genentech and the baselbased roche 
divest themselves of certain holdings or technologies similar to 
the others 
under the merger agreement roche parent of f hoffmanlaroche 
amp co will pay 36 a share for 50 percent of the shares into 
genentech and inject 492 million of capital into the company for 
the other 10 percent 
genentech maker of the heart attack drug tpa will have a cash 
balance of 600 million which it hopes will help it get new 
products on the market 
roche also has the option to buy another 15 percent of genentech 
on the open market it also may buy the rest of genentech over the 
next five years at fixed prices ranging from 38 to 60 
shareholders will get 36 each for half of their shares and new 
redeemable common stock in exchange for the other half a windfall 
of 65 million plus stock 
genentechs stock closed at 29 on the new york stock exchange 
on friday up 1 from thursday the stock had hovered at about 27 
since the announcement of the merger 
genentech founded in 1976 is a world leader in the development 
of biotechnology products and has been profitable every year but 
one since 1979 in 1989 it had earnings of 44 million or 51 
cents a share on revenues were 400 million 
roche holdings a health care company specializing in 
pharmaceutical development and vitamin and chemical manufacturing 
had worldwide sales of 65 billion last year 
the terms of the consent decree with the ftc will appear in the 
us federal register and be subject to public comment for 60 days 
the ftc will then decide whether to make the decree final but 
the public comment period will not prevent genentech and roche from 
putting the deal into effect 
under the decree genentech must divest its 50 percent interest 
in glc associates a partnership formed with lubrizol inc of 
cleveland ohio but currently without employees to develop a 
recombinant process to produce vitamin c roche has a large share 
of the worldwide vitamin c market 
the decree requires roche to divest its technology with respect 
to human growth hormone releasing factor genentech developed and 
markets human growth hormone which is used to treat children with 
pituitary dwarfism 
roche also must grant nonexclusive licenses under its american 
patent rights with respect to cd4igm a potential aids drug in the 
early research stage genentech currently has a similar potential 
aids drug cd4iig in early clinical trials 
officials from both companies have said that genentechs 
management and research will remain independent two roche 
executives armin m kessler roche chief operating officer and 
director and jurgen drews head of roche corporate research will 
hold two seats on genentechs 13seat board of directors 
